  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Energy Sector Management Assistance Programme (ESMAP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The World Bank Energy Sector Management Assistance Programme (ESMAP) is a multi-donor trust fund that provides technical assistance to help shape global energy policies and leverage significant development financing.  It primarily targets six Asian countries (China, India, Indonesia, the Philippines, Pakistan and Vietnam) where the most new, unabated coal-fired power generation is due to begin operation (from 2018 to 2020). ESMAP is influential in advising countries on the clean energy transition, with significant demand for its technical assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
